
title Secure PW Storage

actor User

Website->Website: 1. "A" = new sig keypair
API->API: 2. "B" = new sig keypair
User->Website: 3. enter uid / pw
Website->API: 4. uid, pw, A(uid)

API->API: 5. const salt for enc AES key (c_salt)

API->API: 6. new AES key from input Aes_Key = (SHA256(B(A(uid))), c_salt)

API->API: 7. const iv for enc message (c_iv)
API->API: 8. C(pw) = AES_ENC (c_iv, Aes_Key, pw)

alt enroll

API->DB: 9. Store {"uid", C(pw)}
API->Website: 10. enrolling
end 

alt authn
API->DB: 11. Query ("uid")
DB->API: 12. data (C(pw))

API->API: 13. AES key from input Aes_Key = (SHA256(B(A(uid))), c_salt)

API->API: 14. pw = AES_DEC (c_iv, Aes_Key, C(pw)), i.e. decrypt C(data) and compare
API->Website: 15. pass / fail
end

